data.enText: to deal successfully with a difficulty

data.chText: 她很清楚必须克服哪些困难。
data.enText: She was well aware of the difficulties that had to be surmounted.

data.chText: 处于（某物）上面；置于（某物）顶端
data.enText: to be placed on top of sth

data.chText: 顶端立着一尊雕像的高大的柱子
data.enText: a high column surmounted by a statue

simple_means.memory_skill: sur 上；超；外加 + mount 山 → 登上；超越

tr: be or do something to a greater degree
example: her performance surpasses that of any other student I know
This car outperforms all others in its class

value.def: If you surmount a problem or difficulty, you deal successfully with it.

example.ex: I realized I had to surmount the language barrier.
example.tran: 我意识到我不得不克服语言障碍。

value.def: If something is surmounted by a particular thing, that thing is on top of it.

example.ex: The island is surmounted by a huge black castle.
example.tran: 岛的最高处耸立着一座巨大的黑色城堡。

in 不 + sur 超 + mount 登上；升 + able 能…的 → 不能超过的 → 难以克服的
